column1:
4.6.4.1	
Conservative management 
The individual components of self-management have not been critically evaluated and most recommendations 
are traditionally derived from consensus methodology. Interventions such as those listed below may help with 
nocturia but, for the majority, no quantification of their effect is possible:
•	
reduction of fluid intake at specific times;
•	
avoidance/moderation of intake of caffeine or alcohol;
•	
distraction techniques;
•	
bladder retraining;
•	
pelvic floor muscle training;
•	
reviewing medication;
•	
treatment of constipation.
